 The CEO of PMR Africa, Mr Johan Hattingh, handed over the Diamond Arrow to Editor, Tobie van den Bergh, with Mpumalanga News following in second place. The Middelburg Observer came first after a provincial survey was done on companies or institutions who have achieved the most in stimulating economic growth and development in the province. The winners were chosen by a panel made up of CEO’s, MD’s, business owners, company directors, managers and government officials based in Mpumalanga. PMR Africa is a consultancy and research company based in South Africa. •The purpose of their award ceremony is to create a platform where companies and institutions can be branded as entities with growing potential.  Hawks members sent to jail for fraud WATCH: The Place of Refuge – Once a vibrant village, now a ghost town WATCH: Robbery caught on video, police looking for suspects Three counts of poaching in one week – and the toll keeps rising   • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za